    <text type="letter">
        <body>

            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">431 Stevens st.</name>
                    <date notBefore="1878-01-01" notAfter="1884-01-01" rend="right">Thursday afternoon <lb/>1 <lb/>2 past 2.<ptr target="prc.00085_n1"
                        /></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mrs. Johnston,</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>This is the queer little book, perhaps you may remember I spoke about some weeks
                since. It is odd in form, &amp; may be without attractiveness at first&#8212;but
                somehow I think it real <hi rend="italic">good</hi> &amp; <hi rend="italic">deep</hi>&#8212;(after you
                break the crust &amp; get a little used to it.) My Dear friend I am so sorry to hear
                by Johnny that you are ill, &amp; suffering&#8212;I wish I could send you something,
                or do something for your relief&#8212;</p>

            <closer>
                <signed rend="right">Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
